It’s been almost four weeks since the start of the lockdown. This period has exposed the harsh and devastating realities of people in poor communities. JOHANNESBURG - The ANC has urged its structures to investigate and take action against members involved in misappropriating relief packages and other corrupt activities during the national lockdown. Municipal councillors across the country have been accused of breaking lockdown regulations and in some cases stealing essential goods from the poorest of the poor. READ: SA Schools providing food to pupils, community ANC spokesperson Pule Mabe said all the party's structures have been urged to investigate cases of misappropriation and take action. Mabe said ANC councillors should be seen extending a helping hand to communities during this crisis and should not seek to benefit through corruption. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.